{{Infobox US Ambassador | name= Alberto Martinez Piedra | image=Alberto Piedra with Ronald Reagan.jpg |caption=1984 | imagesize = | order= | ambassador_from=United States | country= Guatemala | term_start= August 17, 1984 | term_end= August 22, 1987 | president= [[Ronald Reagan]] | predecessor = [[Frederic L. Chapin]] | successor = [[James H. Michel]] | birth_date = {{Birth date and age |1926|1|29|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[Cuba]] | spouse= | party= | profession= | religion= }}
'''Alberto Martinez Piedra''' (born January 29, 1926<ref>State Dept Office of the Historian, [https://history.state.gov/departmenthistory/people/piedra-alberto-martinez Alberto Martinez Piedra]</ref>) is the David E. Bentley Professor of Political Economy at [[The Institute of World Politics]].<ref name=IWP>[http://www.iwp.edu/faculty/facultyID.27/profile.asp Alberto M. Piedra]. The Institute of World Politics.</ref>
Dr. Piedra was the Director of the Latin American Institute at [[The Catholic University of America]] from 1965-1982.<ref name=AA>{{Cite web |url=http://www.americanambassadors.org/index.cfm?fuseaction=Members.view&memberid=179 |title=Alberto M. Piedra |access-date=2009-08-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100917153936/http://americanambassadors.org/index.cfm?fuseaction=Members.view&memberid=179 |archive-date=2010-09-17 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> He was the [[United States Ambassador to Guatemala]] (1984–1987).
Piedra has three doctorates - Doctor in Law, 1951, [[University of Havana]]; [[Complutense University of Madrid|University of Madrid]] (1957), and [[Georgetown University]] (1962).<ref name=IWP/> He was Director General of Exports and Imports of the Cuban Ministry of Commerce in 1959; and Technical Assistant of the Department of Economic Development of the Cuban National Council from 1958-1959.<ref name=AA/> He was a Staff Economist at the [[Organization of American States|OAS]] from 1960-1962.<ref name=AA/>
