{{Infobox person | name = Nick Groff | image = | caption = | birth_name = Nick Groff | birth_date = {{birth date and age |1980|4|19}} | birth_place= [[San Jose, California]], U.S. | spouse = {{marriage|Veronique Groff|2004}} | alma_mater= [[University of Nevada, Las Vegas]] | children = 2 | occupation = Paranormal investigator, television personality, musician }}
'''Nicholas Groff''' (born April 19, 1980)<ref name=excerpt>{{cite web|work=The Travel Channel|url=http://www.travelchannel.com/shows/ghost-adventures/articles/nick-groffs-chasing-spirits|title=Nick Groff's Chasing Spirits|accessdate=December 6, 2017}}</ref> is an American [[paranormal investigation|paranormal investigator]], musician, and television personality. Groff is currently the lead investigator for the television series ''[[Paranormal Lockdown]]'' and the ''Ghosts of Shepherdstown''. He was a co-investigator and executive producer of ''[[Ghost Adventures]]'', as well as an editor and cameraman for the show from seasons 1–10. Groff was an executive producer for a show on the [[Travel Channel]] called ''Vegas Stripped'', a behind-the-scenes look at the operations of the [[South Point Hotel, Casino & Spa]] in [[Las Vegas, Nevada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/company/co0370647/?ref_=tt_dt_co|title=Groff Entertainment}}</ref>
==Early life== Groff was born April 19, 1980 in [[San Jose, California]], and grew up in [[Nashua, New Hampshire]].<ref name=excerpt/> He graduated from [[Pelham High School (New Hampshire)|Pelham High School]] in New Hampshire and later studied film at the [[University of Nevada, Las Vegas]], where he met Aaron Goodwin. At the age of eight he fell out of a tree in the yard of his family's home in [[Salem, New Hampshire]], which Groff described as "a near-death experience".
Two years later, while at home alone, he says he saw a ghostly figure of a [[African Americans|black]] man. In a 2012 interview, Groff questioned, "Was it my imagination? Or was it something from my accident that made me more open to their [[African-American culture|world]]?"<ref name="lex">{{cite news |url=http://www.kentucky.com/2012/09/27/2352471/scarefest-2012-ghost-adventures.html#storylink=misearch |title=Scarefest 2012: 'Ghost Adventures' host fell into his career |last=Copley |first=Rich |date=September 27, 2012 |work=[[Lexington Herald-Leader]] |publisher=[[The McClatchy Company]]}}</ref>
Groff befriended Bagans during his wedding in Las Vegas.<ref name="lvrj">{{cite news |url=http://www.lvrj.com/living/paranormal-encounters-spook--ghost-adventures--trio-104659404.html |title=Life on the Couch: Paranormal encounters spook 'Ghost Adventures' trio |last=Lawrence |first=Christopher |date=October 10, 2010 |work=[[Las Vegas Review-Journal]] |publisher=[[Stephens Media (newspapers)|Stephens Media]]}}</ref><ref name="nashua">{{cite news |url=http://www.nashuatelegraph.com/livinglifestyles/882559-224/former-nashuan-has-successful-tv-series-hunting.html |title=Former Nashuan has successful TV series hunting ghosts |last=Meighan |first=Patrick |date=October 17, 2010 |work=[[The Telegraph (Nashua)|Nashua Telegraph]] |publisher=Telegraph Publishing Company |accessdate=17 October 2010 |location=[[Nashua, New Hampshire]]}}</ref> Groff claims he was [[spirit possession|possessed]] by an entity at the [[Moon River Brewing Company]] in [[Savannah, Georgia]] and says it was one of his "most life-changing experiences".<ref>{{cite web |title=Ghostly encounters from Moon River |url=http://www.travelchannel.com/TV_Shows/Ghost_Adventures/Video/Ghostly_Encounters_From_Moon_River |publisher=[[Travel Channel]] |accessdate=2010-05-01}}</ref> According to Groff, an encounter with a female spirit at the [[Linda Vista Community Hospital]] in East Los Angeles, California gave him insights into life after death. Groff was allegedly possessed in [[Natchez, Mississippi]] during the investigation of [[King's Tavern]].
==''Ghost Adventures''== {{Main|Ghost Adventures}} In 2004, Groff teamed up with [[Zak Bagans]] and [[Ghost Adventures#Aaron Goodwin|Aaron Goodwin]] to produce a documentary-style film called ''[[Ghost Adventures (2004)|Ghost Adventures]]''. On November 24, 2014, Groff announced that he would not be returning to ''Ghost Adventures'' for the upcoming season.
==Other projects== Groff has since produced his own series titled ''[[Ghost Stalkers]]'', and is currently starring in another show of his ''[[Paranormal Lockdown]]'', where he is the lead investigator.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.axs.com/nick-groff-tells-ghost-adventures-fans-he-is-leaving-the-show-30922|title=Nick Groff tells 'Ghost Adventures' fans he is leaving the show|date=December 1, 2014|accessdate=June 24, 2015}}</ref> He also hosts the ''Ghosts of Shepherdstown'' series on [[Destination America]]; the first season in 2016, and the second in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.destinationamerica.com/tv-shows/ghosts-of-shepherdstown/about-the-ghosts-of-shepherdstown-team/|title=About the Ghosts of Shepherdstown}}</ref> Groff released two albums titled ''The Other Side'' and ''Spiritual War''.The lyrics recall Groff's spiritual journey.<ref name="Bryan">{{cite web|title=Nick Groff|url=http://bryguysworld.wordpress.com/nick-groff/|work=Bryan's World – My Life and the GAC|publisher=Bryan's World – My Life and the GAC|accessdate=7 June 2012|author=BG|year=2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120316041932/http://bryguysworld.wordpress.com/nick-groff/|archivedate=16 March 2012|df=}}</ref> He also has a clothing line named "Phantom Collection".<ref>phantomcollectionclothing.com</ref>
==Personal life== Groff married his wife Veronique, in 2004, and the couple reside outside [[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]]<ref name=shock>{{cite web|work=Shock Ya!|url=http://www.shockya.com/news/2016/10/30/new-york-comic-con-2016-interview-nick-groff-katrina-weidman-and-rob-saffi-talk-paranormal-lockdown/|title=New York Comic-Con 2016 Interview: Nick Groff, Katrina Weidman and Rob Saffi Talk Paranormal Lockdown |author=Benardello, Karen|date=October 30, 2016|accessdate=December 6, 2017}}</ref> with their two daughters.<ref name="Bryan" />
